WEBVTT

00:02.305 --> 00:05.085
♪ You are my sunshine... ♪

00:05.781 --> 00:08.421
♪ My only sunshine... ♪

00:09.468 --> 00:11.734
♪ You make me happy ♪

00:11.759 --> 00:13.921
♪ When skies are gray... ♪

00:13.946 --> 00:14.946
(gasps softly)

00:16.382 --> 00:17.253
Wow.

00:17.288 --> 00:19.773
- (laughs)
- Wow.

00:23.953 --> 00:24.953
Mm.

00:31.851 --> 00:32.867
I'll write.

00:34.257 --> 00:35.343
Every day.

00:35.672 --> 00:36.335
Okay.

00:36.360 --> 00:39.195
- ♪ You are my sunshine... ♪
- All right, Junior.

00:39.220 --> 00:42.664
- ♪ My only sunshine... ♪
- I'll see you soon.

00:42.843 --> 00:45.609
- ♪ You make me happy ♪
- (knocking)

00:46.218 --> 00:48.320
♪ When skies are gray ♪

00:50.140 --> 00:52.980
♪ You'll never know, dear ♪

00:53.590 --> 00:56.066
♪ How much I love you ♪

00:56.526 --> 00:57.800
(gasps softly)

00:57.965 --> 01:02.707
♪ Please don't take my sunshine away. ♪

01:03.191 --> 01:05.120
We're going to be okay.

01:05.894 --> 01:08.207
We're going to be okay, William.

01:09.260 --> 01:10.550
(wheezes softly)

01:13.582 --> 01:15.752
<i>- BETH: I think it's a terrible idea.
- RANDALL: Beth.</i>

01:15.777 --> 01:17.308
BETH: No, he needs to
hear this, Randall.

01:17.332 --> 01:19.782
That's why we came here
today, isn't it, Dr. Lee?

01:19.910 --> 01:21.347
I think it would be helpful if...

01:21.372 --> 01:23.402
One week ago, you had a breakdown.

01:23.660 --> 01:25.519
Your blood pressure
was through the roof.

01:25.544 --> 01:27.323
Your vision was going in and out.

01:27.357 --> 01:28.524
And then paralysis.

01:28.558 --> 01:30.043
Not to mention the tremors.

01:30.371 --> 01:31.629
It was scary.

01:31.731 --> 01:34.433
And you've only been out of
the hospital for five days.

01:34.467 --> 01:36.918
And now he wants to pick up
and take his father, who...

01:36.943 --> 01:38.957
- Beth...
- Mm-mm, not even close to done.

01:38.982 --> 01:43.075
His father, who is in the throes
of stage IV cancer, no less,

01:43.379 --> 01:45.786
- on a cross-country road trip.
- Memphis isn't cross-country.

01:45.810 --> 01:46.793
- Oh, well.
- It's not.

01:46.818 --> 01:48.449
Memphis is not next door. It... (sighs)

01:48.558 --> 01:49.511
You done?

01:49.536 --> 01:50.925
- I am done.
- Okay.

01:51.996 --> 01:54.097
- I got a little hot.
- You always get a little hot.

01:54.122 --> 01:56.223
- Mm-mm, don't be cute.
- Okay.

01:56.380 --> 01:58.215
Well, you two sure are adorable.

01:58.663 --> 01:59.933
- I know.
- We know.

02:00.757 --> 02:02.511
Look, Dr. Lee, um...

02:03.458 --> 02:05.996
I've been feeling much
better, as you know.

02:06.798 --> 02:08.363
I've taken some time off work.

02:08.388 --> 02:09.854
I've been checking in with you.

02:09.880 --> 02:11.941
My stress tests have been good.

02:14.441 --> 02:16.277
My father doesn't have
a lot of time left.

02:16.732 --> 02:19.668
And he'd very much like
to show me where he's from.

02:19.935 --> 02:22.449
Maybe even introduce me to
some extended family...

02:22.474 --> 02:23.980
- Mm.
- ... which, for me, would be

02:24.005 --> 02:25.215
a really big deal, you know?

02:25.861 --> 02:28.488
Now, my wife is naturally

02:28.720 --> 02:30.941
and adorably concerned.

02:32.894 --> 02:34.738
Curious your thoughts on the matter.

02:35.704 --> 02:36.738
♪

02:39.415 --> 02:40.573
Let's go.

02:44.240 --> 02:45.402
I saw that.

02:49.709 --> 02:50.709
(sighs)

02:51.325 --> 02:54.019
♪ Hey, oh, Lord ♪

02:55.229 --> 02:57.582
♪ Hey, oh, Lord ♪

