03:17.317 --> 03:18.449
WILLIAM: Hey.

03:19.425 --> 03:21.035
We're getting an early start.

03:21.957 --> 03:23.050
Okay.

03:23.644 --> 03:26.425
You keep up with your chess
while I'm gone, you hear?

03:27.347 --> 03:28.190
Okay.

03:28.215 --> 03:29.472
Okay, then.

03:30.504 --> 03:31.699
Go back to sleep.

03:36.669 --> 03:37.863
♪

03:54.308 --> 03:55.496
BETH: You take care of him.

03:56.621 --> 03:57.621
Of course.

03:58.433 --> 03:59.980
Take good care of you, too.

04:01.145 --> 04:02.504
I'll send you a postcard.

04:02.529 --> 04:03.529
(engine starts)

04:03.918 --> 04:04.918
I love you.

04:05.249 --> 04:06.249
I love you, too.

04:06.584 --> 04:09.090
All right, don't drive too fast, okay?

04:09.522 --> 04:10.597
Come on.

04:11.879 --> 04:12.980
♪

04:20.606 --> 04:22.496
We gonna do this old school, sir.

04:22.521 --> 04:25.743
Jersey to Memphis...
no navigation, no Waze.

04:25.778 --> 04:27.613
Got these maps online.

04:27.638 --> 04:29.580
Now, William, you're
gonna be my lead navigator.

04:29.615 --> 04:31.636
All that I ask is that
you stay ahead of me.

04:31.661 --> 04:34.019
We got a turn coming up,
let's get ahead of it.

04:34.044 --> 04:35.348
Got to merge onto a busy highway,

04:35.372 --> 04:36.786
- give me a heads-up.
- Let me see those.

04:36.810 --> 04:38.144
Yep. Here you go.

04:40.255 --> 04:41.316
Hey!

04:41.879 --> 04:43.293
Hey, just drive, son.

04:43.318 --> 04:44.824
- We'll get there.
- (sighs)

04:45.831 --> 04:47.004
Just drive.

04:49.256 --> 04:50.300
♪

04:51.488 --> 04:56.097
synced and corrected by susinz
*www.addic7ed.com*

05:14.215 --> 05:17.317
WILLIAM (quietly):
♪ You are my sunshine ♪

05:17.351 --> 05:20.687
♪ My only sunshine ♪

05:20.722 --> 05:23.890
♪ You make me happy ♪

05:23.925 --> 05:26.359
♪ When skies are gray ♪

05:26.394 --> 05:29.196
♪ You'll never know, dear ♪

05:29.230 --> 05:31.932
♪ How much I love you ♪

05:31.966 --> 05:34.701
♪ Please don't take ♪

05:34.736 --> 05:36.629
♪ My sunshine away. ♪

05:36.654 --> 05:39.338
MAN (over P.A.): <i>Now boarding
track two to Pittsburgh.</i>

05:39.363 --> 05:40.840
I hate that you're leaving.

05:41.332 --> 05:43.113
Well, Grandma's not doing well.

05:43.316 --> 05:45.652
So you have to drop everything
to go take care of her?

05:45.677 --> 05:47.293
Yes, William, I do.

05:47.685 --> 05:48.972
That's what family does.

05:50.315 --> 05:52.011
Pittsburgh isn't that far.

05:52.379 --> 05:53.629
It's pretty far.

05:53.855 --> 05:55.519
Oh, it's pretty damn far, isn't it?

05:55.957 --> 05:57.090
(both laugh)

05:58.192 --> 06:00.699
You be safe. You be good.

06:01.456 --> 06:03.152
If you want me to come, I will.

06:03.177 --> 06:04.444
No, no.

06:04.794 --> 06:06.886
I've kept you to myself long enough.

06:07.802 --> 06:09.236
Time to spread your wings.

06:09.270 --> 06:10.737
Focus on your art,

06:10.772 --> 06:11.886
your music.

06:12.606 --> 06:14.121
You have a gift, baby.

06:15.035 --> 06:18.300
You have so many beautiful
futures in front of you.

06:19.941 --> 06:22.793
Make sure you pick a
good one for me, okay?

06:23.300 --> 06:24.300
I will.

06:25.097 --> 06:26.994
And make sure that
charmer cousin of yours

06:27.019 --> 06:29.019
follows your lead,
not the other way around.

06:29.044 --> 06:30.418
(chuckles): Okay.

06:34.629 --> 06:36.705
You're the best thing
that ever happened to me.

06:36.730 --> 06:38.168
- Oh, Mom.
- So I just... Okay.

06:38.193 --> 06:40.535
I'm not gonna cry. I'm
not, I'm not crying.

06:41.002 --> 06:42.183
Okay. Bye, now, baby.

06:42.208 --> 06:43.355
- Bye, Mama.
- Bye.

06:45.695 --> 06:46.722
♪

06:58.186 --> 06:59.785
WILLIAM (chuckles): Oh, man.

07:00.269 --> 07:02.571
I hope the ducks are
still at the Peabody.

07:04.418 --> 07:07.627
My uncle used to work there
as a bellman when it was segregated.

07:07.662 --> 07:09.050
And he would sneak me in.

07:09.075 --> 07:10.075
Hmm.

07:11.199 --> 07:13.480
Man, I sure would like
you to see those ducks.

07:15.902 --> 07:17.911
You want a banana? Something
to put in your stomach?

07:17.935 --> 07:19.207
No, no, I'll be fine.

07:19.450 --> 07:22.527
My God, woman packed a half
a produce department in here.

07:23.597 --> 07:24.910
With instructions.

07:25.308 --> 07:26.379
(chuckles)

07:26.761 --> 07:28.347
She worries about you.

07:28.996 --> 07:30.191
Yeah, that she does.

07:31.120 --> 07:32.199
That she does.

07:33.371 --> 07:35.949
You know, I didn't believe
her at first when she told me

07:35.974 --> 07:37.527
about you having a breakdown.

07:39.072 --> 07:41.004
Is it okay to call it a breakdown?

07:42.675 --> 07:44.027
Lots of names for it.

07:44.411 --> 07:46.871
Anxiety attack, mental distress,

07:46.957 --> 07:50.488
nervous exhaustion,
stress-induced trauma.

07:51.138 --> 07:52.605
You choose.

07:54.543 --> 07:56.574
It was quite a shock to
see you so vulnerable.

07:57.172 --> 07:58.933
The night Kevin brought you home...

08:00.527 --> 08:03.386
I mean, it... it's hard to fathom.

08:03.802 --> 08:05.675
You seem to have it all together.

08:07.027 --> 08:08.136
Too together.

08:08.161 --> 08:09.795
Always been like that.

08:11.035 --> 08:13.918
Just putting the pressure on myself,
ever since I was a little boy.

08:15.129 --> 08:16.277
My father...

08:16.754 --> 08:18.715
- he kept it in check.
- Mm-hmm.

08:20.372 --> 08:22.199
Whenever I'd get too in my head,

08:22.660 --> 08:25.996
<i>he'd take his hands and put
them on both sides of my head,</i>

08:26.021 --> 08:27.466
<i>and he'd just say... </i>

08:27.579 --> 08:29.713
There you go, breathe with me.

08:30.544 --> 08:31.957
(breathing rhythmically)

08:31.982 --> 08:35.293
<i>And we'd just sit there,
just breathing together... </i>

08:35.672 --> 08:37.139
(both exhale)

08:38.347 --> 08:39.605
... until it passed.

08:43.658 --> 08:44.738
Wow.

08:46.508 --> 08:48.910
What was he like? Your father.

08:50.121 --> 08:52.558
Larger than life, I guess.

08:53.230 --> 08:54.215
(laughs)

08:54.240 --> 08:56.875
He had this really great laugh.

08:57.145 --> 08:59.816
It's like, when he laughed,
it was like, uh...

09:00.144 --> 09:02.222
like it almost surprised him, you know?

09:03.170 --> 09:05.769
Like it surprised him that
he could laugh so freely.

09:08.949 --> 09:10.082
Where is he buried?

09:10.107 --> 09:11.793
Uh, he's cremated.

09:12.547 --> 09:13.769
Kate has his ashes.

09:14.783 --> 09:17.668
But we spread some of them near
a tree at his favorite park,

09:17.693 --> 09:20.090
so that's kind of his
official resting place.

09:23.892 --> 09:25.207
Think we could go?

09:26.519 --> 09:28.269
I'd like to pay my respects.

09:29.707 --> 09:30.832
I'd like that, actually.

09:32.131 --> 09:33.347
But not this trip.

09:33.529 --> 09:35.597
- It's a half day out of the way.
- Randall.

09:38.074 --> 09:40.394
Put your window down, turn up the music.

09:41.010 --> 09:42.660
Take me to meet your father.

09:43.306 --> 09:44.457
♪

09:54.052 --> 09:55.332
Give me a minute.

09:56.992 --> 09:58.144
Uh, yeah.

09:58.625 --> 09:59.660
Sure.

10:11.147 --> 10:12.147
Thank you.

10:13.212 --> 10:14.824
For doing what I couldn't.

10:16.488 --> 10:18.816
For raising him to be the man he is.

10:20.628 --> 10:22.980
I'm sorry I didn't get a
chance to meet you, brother.

10:24.485 --> 10:26.754
I would have liked to
have heard that laugh.

10:26.863 --> 10:27.894
(chuckles)

10:29.042 --> 10:31.457
I would have liked to
have met my son's father.

10:40.902 --> 10:41.902
Yeah.

10:42.884 --> 10:43.917
Cool.

10:53.095 --> 10:54.199
I like him.

10:56.420 --> 10:59.074
Pay your respects, and then
we should get on the road.

10:59.378 --> 11:00.410
(panting softly)

11:08.067 --> 11:09.113
♪

11:13.004 --> 11:16.183
♪ Uh... huh ♪

11:17.466 --> 11:19.957
♪ My honey and me ♪

11:21.004 --> 11:23.518
♪ Hold us together... ♪

11:23.543 --> 11:26.580
DOROTHY: <i>"Dear William, I
received your beautiful poem,</i>

11:26.605 --> 11:27.871
<i>and it gave me comfort.</i>

11:28.277 --> 11:31.354
<i>Please stop being so hard on
yourself for not making the funeral.</i>

11:31.410 --> 11:34.666
<i>Grandma wouldn't have
wanted you to come so far.</i>

11:34.691 --> 11:37.768
<i>I'm going to stay here for a bit
and take care of her affairs."</i>

11:37.793 --> 11:39.604
<i>"Dear William, guess what.</i>

11:39.629 --> 11:42.104
<i>I got a job down at the library.</i>

11:42.129 --> 11:45.502
<i>Pays well and I get to
be around books all day.</i>

11:45.527 --> 11:47.580
<i>I know I wasn't planning on staying,</i>

11:47.605 --> 11:49.230
<i>but the money sure is gonna help... "</i>

11:49.265 --> 11:52.901
<i>"Dear William, it was so nice
talking to you last week.</i>

11:52.935 --> 11:55.611
<i>I'm so glad to hear the
band is doing so well</i>

11:55.636 --> 11:58.254
<i>and that your cousin
is staying focused."</i>

11:58.550 --> 11:59.424
(groans)

11:59.449 --> 12:01.636
<i>"No shame in playing
great covers, William,</i>

12:01.661 --> 12:03.160
<i>- remember that."</i>
- (whooping)

12:03.810 --> 12:05.082
<i>"I miss you, baby.</i>

12:05.238 --> 12:07.644
<i>I'm going to make it back
soon to see you play."</i>

12:07.669 --> 12:08.870
Come on, baby.

12:08.905 --> 12:10.285
(bluesy rock song ends)

12:10.310 --> 12:11.675
(cheering, laughter)

12:13.217 --> 12:16.185
Mm. So I tell her. I say,
I say, "Sweetheart, look,

12:16.449 --> 12:18.363
you're a once-in-a-lifetime
beauty, no question,

12:18.388 --> 12:19.934
but you're talking about
spending the rest of your life

12:19.958 --> 12:22.613
with me, and... as much as
I love a quality fillet,

12:22.638 --> 12:24.673
I just ain't ready to give
up that whole rack of ribs!"

12:24.697 --> 12:25.925
You know what I'm saying?

12:25.950 --> 12:27.738
Yeah, I like 'em wet, not dry, right?

12:27.763 --> 12:28.763
(laughs)

12:30.322 --> 12:31.705
Hey, William?

12:31.854 --> 12:33.013
Uh, uh...

12:33.038 --> 12:33.861
Oh, see?

12:33.886 --> 12:35.635
My cousin the nun. (laughs)

12:36.716 --> 12:38.517
Hey, man, y'all let him be now.

12:38.542 --> 12:40.176
If we was all as good as my cuz,

12:40.201 --> 12:42.002
Memphis would be a hell of a lot safer.

12:42.027 --> 12:44.299
A lot less fun, but a
hell of a lot safer, right?

12:44.420 --> 12:45.455
(laughs)

12:45.734 --> 12:46.893
Here you go, baby.

12:48.378 --> 12:49.697
Hey. (sighs)

12:51.275 --> 12:53.744
Hey, look, I'm sorry about
teasing you back there, cuz.

12:53.769 --> 12:55.903
You know, um, I get a little
loosey-goosey when I...

12:55.928 --> 12:57.697
(inhales sharply) you know.

12:57.722 --> 12:58.822
(both laugh)

13:01.002 --> 13:03.111
I've been writing, and
I think it might be good.

13:03.783 --> 13:04.783
Come on.

13:05.224 --> 13:06.588
(sniffles) Let's see here.

13:16.578 --> 13:17.815
Well, um...

13:19.229 --> 13:21.104
it's about damn time, boy!

13:21.408 --> 13:23.211
Been waiting on your talented skinny ass

13:23.245 --> 13:24.316
to take us to the big time.

13:24.340 --> 13:25.455
Hey, boys!

13:25.619 --> 13:27.393
Hey, kid's got something. Come on.

13:27.418 --> 13:28.495
- Right now?
- Yeah, right now.

13:28.519 --> 13:30.065
Drinks down. Come on, let's go.

13:30.479 --> 13:31.502
Okay.

13:32.637 --> 13:34.580
Waiting two years for
you to hand me something.

13:35.057 --> 13:36.393
I'm not sleeping on this.

13:36.646 --> 13:38.190
All right, give me a G.

13:38.472 --> 13:39.479
Yeah.

13:41.682 --> 13:42.962
(band playing gentle soul music)

13:44.158 --> 13:46.288
♪ Standing at the station ♪

13:46.892 --> 13:49.760
♪ We don't know what to say ♪

13:54.627 --> 13:56.650
♪ Looking out the window ♪

13:57.027 --> 14:00.627
♪ As you're rolling away ♪

14:02.418 --> 14:06.041
♪ If I'm gonna be alone ♪

14:12.478 --> 14:15.744
♪ Let it be with you ♪

14:16.299 --> 14:18.649
You officially ended our
days as a cover band, boy!

14:18.674 --> 14:20.017
On the five!

14:20.046 --> 14:21.924
(band continues playing soul music)

14:25.947 --> 14:27.947
♪ Mother, don't you cry ♪

14:28.516 --> 14:31.351
♪ We're gonna be all right ♪

14:36.398 --> 14:39.088
♪ Open up your suitcase ♪

14:39.113 --> 14:42.603
♪ When you get there tonight ♪

14:44.159 --> 14:48.296
♪ You're not alone ♪

14:50.344 --> 14:52.502
♪ I'm always ♪

14:53.301 --> 14:57.471
♪ Always here with you ♪

15:06.072 --> 15:08.388
♪ So don't give up on me ♪

15:10.879 --> 15:13.689
♪ I'll never give up on you ♪

15:16.336 --> 15:18.885
♪ Everything's gonna be all right ♪

15:21.044 --> 15:24.033
♪ I know you believe it, too ♪

15:25.831 --> 15:31.307
♪ If I'm gonna be alone... ♪

15:35.530 --> 15:39.111
♪ Then let it be with you ♪

15:41.500 --> 15:43.752
♪ Look up ♪

15:44.129 --> 15:47.338
♪ Not down ♪

15:47.363 --> 15:48.588
(crowd cheers)

15:49.375 --> 15:52.478
♪ It all comes around ♪

15:55.043 --> 15:57.166
♪ Even when you're gone ♪

15:59.438 --> 16:02.106
♪ We can always come back to this ♪

16:02.131 --> 16:03.353
(crowd cheers)

16:04.111 --> 16:06.986
♪ We can always come back to this ♪

16:09.174 --> 16:10.572
♪ We can always ♪

16:10.597 --> 16:13.580
♪ Always, always, always ♪

16:13.982 --> 16:16.385
♪ Always come back to this. ♪

16:16.410 --> 16:17.911
(song ends, crowd cheering)

16:26.511 --> 16:27.747
Don't be trying it.

16:27.955 --> 16:29.222
(chuckles)

16:30.093 --> 16:31.865
- Hey.
- Hey, how you doing?

16:32.224 --> 16:34.482
Hey, you gonna go out with us tonight?

16:40.771 --> 16:42.318
Nah, I'm-I'm gonna call it a night.

16:42.343 --> 16:45.224
Ugh! Man, you know all this
'cause of you, cuz, right?

16:45.249 --> 16:48.122
You should try to
enjoy it more. William!

16:48.271 --> 16:49.591
I know. (chuckles)

16:49.616 --> 16:50.841
Uh, ladies ready?

16:51.031 --> 16:53.032
Oh, come on. I got somewhere we can go.

16:53.057 --> 16:54.658
MAN: William?
- Nice. This is nice.

16:54.802 --> 16:56.119
Your ma's on the phone.

16:59.631 --> 17:00.638
Hi, Mama.

17:04.928 --> 17:06.090
Okay.

17:18.568 --> 17:20.130
Why are you making the bed?

17:21.069 --> 17:22.396
I like making the bed.

17:23.182 --> 17:24.560
But it's a hotel.

17:24.585 --> 17:26.068
It's a <i>motel,</i>

17:26.816 --> 17:29.990
and this is a bed, and I like making it.

17:30.990 --> 17:33.505
Someone else would make
it, is all I'm saying.

17:33.530 --> 17:36.849
Well, I guess that's one less thing
for someone else to do. All right?

17:38.878 --> 17:39.966
(groans)

17:42.946 --> 17:44.060
(groans loudly)

17:46.893 --> 17:47.893
Hold on.

17:48.417 --> 17:49.638
(groans)

17:49.907 --> 17:51.044
Easy does it.

17:53.213 --> 17:54.357
Hey.

17:54.480 --> 17:55.622
(groans)

17:57.951 --> 17:59.482
(breathing deeply)

18:02.204 --> 18:03.326
(groans softly)

18:08.321 --> 18:10.044
You ready to go back to Memphis?

18:10.084 --> 18:12.418
("Feels So Good" by
Junior Kimbrough playing)

18:18.595 --> 18:21.177
♪ Ooh-wee, my girl,
you know I love you ♪

18:21.702 --> 18:23.247
♪ Yes, I love you ♪

18:23.272 --> 18:25.716
♪ When you curl your
lovely loving arms ♪

18:26.170 --> 18:30.365
♪ All around me, girl,
you make me feel good ♪

18:30.390 --> 18:32.927
♪ Now, girl, I feel good... feel good ♪

18:32.952 --> 18:34.654
Well, we're here.

18:34.679 --> 18:36.615
Yes, we are. (chuckles)

18:37.294 --> 18:40.802
Oh, wow. Soulsville right
there is where I grew up.

18:40.827 --> 18:42.912
Used to have a
girlfriend lived up there.

18:42.937 --> 18:44.177
- (Randall laughs)
- See?

18:44.202 --> 18:45.794
Fresh meats that you could actually go

18:45.819 --> 18:47.449
- (laughs)
- and pick out the chicken.

18:47.474 --> 18:49.543
- He would kill the chicken...
- What?

18:49.568 --> 18:50.888
... defeather it, clean it,

18:50.913 --> 18:53.490
- and then wrap it up for you.
- I think I'd be traumatized.

18:53.515 --> 18:56.068
That's how we used to buy
chickens back in the day.

18:56.093 --> 18:57.994
William, you know where
you want to go first?

18:58.019 --> 18:58.651
I do.

18:59.005 --> 19:00.646
Should I plug it into the GPS, or... ?

19:00.671 --> 19:02.068
No need to plug anything in.

19:02.093 --> 19:04.021
- Just make a left right up here.
- All right.

19:04.046 --> 19:05.404
♪ Girl, I feel good ♪

19:05.429 --> 19:06.544
♪ Feel good ♪

19:06.569 --> 19:10.255
♪ Well, that feels so good... ♪

19:20.060 --> 19:21.951
This is where I used
to live with my mother.

19:22.740 --> 19:25.919
- Just the two of you?
- Always just the two of us, yeah.

19:29.853 --> 19:31.068
Looks different.

19:32.353 --> 19:34.247
Well, 40-plus years will do that.

19:37.707 --> 19:38.826
What are you thinking?

19:41.223 --> 19:43.162
I can't stop looking at that door.

19:44.278 --> 19:46.763
Used to be two of 'em.
Now one is bricked up.

19:48.338 --> 19:50.333
Isn't that a strange thing to focus on?

19:50.358 --> 19:53.154
All these years, and it's
a door that's hanging me up.

19:58.671 --> 20:00.177
I used to have a bit of a 'fro.

20:01.008 --> 20:03.950
- Nah.
- Yeah, into my 30s, actually.

20:04.313 --> 20:07.271
But then I made partner, life
started to get more serious.

20:07.755 --> 20:09.912
Needed to update the look.

20:11.922 --> 20:13.490
Oh, Tess was about three at the time.

20:14.103 --> 20:17.539
And when I came home from
the barbershop that Saturday,

20:17.564 --> 20:19.198
clean-shaven, clean-cut,

20:19.223 --> 20:21.888
she took one look at
me and started bawling.

20:21.913 --> 20:22.865
(laughs): No.

20:22.890 --> 20:25.240
Damn near hyperventilated, the poor kid.

20:26.372 --> 20:28.130
And it wasn't that she
didn't recognize me.

20:28.416 --> 20:29.583
It just took her a minute

20:29.608 --> 20:31.521
to see past the bricked-up
front door, was all.

20:37.091 --> 20:39.708
- I think I want to go inside.
- Oh. Okay.

20:40.240 --> 20:41.747
Well, there's probably people

20:41.772 --> 20:43.014
- who live there now, so...
- I want to see if my

20:43.038 --> 20:45.193
- treasure is still there.
- Your what? Hey.

20:45.218 --> 20:46.218
(knocks)

20:46.961 --> 20:48.927
- Afternoon.
- Afternoon.

20:49.255 --> 20:54.068
Um, you don't know us, but my
father grew up in this house,

20:54.786 --> 20:58.224
and we were wondering if
he could take a look around.

21:00.325 --> 21:01.810
This really means a lot to him.

21:01.835 --> 21:04.161
- We appreciate it.
- No worries, we're happy to.

21:06.911 --> 21:09.099
- What the hell is he doing?
- I don't know. I'm not...

21:09.124 --> 21:11.279
Hey, William, maybe you shouldn't
distort...

21:11.671 --> 21:12.825
My treasure.

21:13.252 --> 21:14.252
Yeah?

21:14.435 --> 21:15.638
Well, what is it?

21:16.616 --> 21:18.060
A few toys and three quarters.

21:21.810 --> 21:23.021
Yeah, no, I see that. I mean...

21:23.045 --> 21:24.958
I put them here once,

21:25.547 --> 21:29.279
and after all these years
later, they're still here.

21:31.740 --> 21:33.169
Isn't that something?

21:33.763 --> 21:37.646
Isn't it strange how the world
sticks and moves like that?

21:40.529 --> 21:41.529
Uh...

21:42.483 --> 21:43.626
Uh...

21:44.130 --> 21:45.974
Okay, so...

21:46.868 --> 21:48.035
... here's your brick.

21:48.092 --> 21:49.957
I didn't know that was
gonna happen but...

21:49.982 --> 21:53.044
thank you, folks. God bless you.
Appreciate it.

21:55.146 --> 21:56.107
(door closes)

21:56.137 --> 21:57.512
♪

22:00.568 --> 22:03.183
- RANDALL (chuckles): Ooh-hoo-hoo.
- Now we talking eats, son.

22:03.208 --> 22:04.277
I know what I'm getting.

22:04.302 --> 22:06.496
I try not to eat too
much pork, you understand.

22:06.521 --> 22:07.435
God bless you.

22:07.460 --> 22:08.460
Bon appétit.

22:09.224 --> 22:10.191
Still the same.

22:10.225 --> 22:11.192
(chuckles)

22:11.226 --> 22:12.173
(laughs)

22:12.198 --> 22:13.736
- Let 'em know.
- He loves it.

22:13.962 --> 22:15.930
RANDALL: They're making more meat.

22:15.964 --> 22:18.042
RANDALL: I remember the first time
my dad took me to the barbershop.

22:18.066 --> 22:19.367
WILLIAM: I remember, too, man.

22:19.401 --> 22:21.535
- My barber was named Cliff.
- Cliff.

22:21.570 --> 22:24.355
I'll never forget him, 'cause he used
to always threaten to cut my ears off.

22:24.379 --> 22:25.272
(laughs)

22:25.307 --> 22:28.376
Instead of a Gumby, I had a
ramp low-to-high, back like this.

22:28.410 --> 22:30.145
- It certainly ain't the Jheri curl.
- (laughter)

22:30.169 --> 22:31.941
I got the good stuff, man.

22:32.247 --> 22:33.955
- MAN: Look good, man.
- Yes, sir.

22:33.980 --> 22:37.118
♪ Ooh-wee, you know
I love you now, baby ♪

22:37.152 --> 22:38.832
♪ Yeah, I love you ♪

22:39.154 --> 22:40.825
♪ When you curl your
lovely loving arms... ♪

22:40.849 --> 22:42.316
This is... this is the one.

22:42.991 --> 22:45.519
♪ Girl, you kiss
me, you hold me... ♪

22:45.574 --> 22:47.879
WILLIAM: This is the
original water fountain

22:47.904 --> 22:50.019
that they kept here
for its history lesson.

22:50.044 --> 22:52.237
That was white and this was black.

22:52.262 --> 22:55.144
You know what? I've been living
with white people for a long time.

22:55.169 --> 22:57.405
Oh, my God, you're in trouble now, son.

22:57.769 --> 22:58.879
(exhales)

22:59.191 --> 23:01.152
- Think you should have a taste.
- Think I should.

23:01.177 --> 23:02.433
- For old times.
- Why not?

23:03.089 --> 23:04.636
- Yeah.
- I'm doing it.

23:06.295 --> 23:07.295
(laughs)

23:08.440 --> 23:09.695
(smacking lips)

23:09.720 --> 23:11.151
(exhales)

23:11.176 --> 23:12.354
(both laughing)

23:13.199 --> 23:14.233
(car doors close)

23:19.127 --> 23:21.128
(blues music playing over speakers)

23:24.776 --> 23:26.753
Mm. (chuckles)

23:26.778 --> 23:27.878
(pats stool)

23:27.903 --> 23:29.151
Willy.

23:29.176 --> 23:31.144
Yeah, I know the timing isn't great,

23:31.169 --> 23:32.800
with us taking off and all.

23:32.825 --> 23:34.714
Hey, your mama needs you, all right?

23:34.739 --> 23:36.714
Never apologize for
taking care of family.

23:37.652 --> 23:39.394
I won't-won't be gone long.

23:41.042 --> 23:42.167
Mama's a tank.

23:42.300 --> 23:43.784
Yeah, she the bullets, too.

23:43.809 --> 23:45.277
(chuckles): Uh-uh.

23:45.456 --> 23:47.761
I'm gonna come back with 60 new songs.

23:47.786 --> 23:50.542
60? All right, I'm gonna
hold you to that, cuz.

23:50.567 --> 23:51.659
(chuckles)

23:52.061 --> 23:53.061
Mm.

23:55.347 --> 23:56.829
- Here.
- No, come on...

23:56.854 --> 23:59.034
Aw, come on, man, take
it, take it, take it.

23:59.581 --> 24:02.141
- I will give it back to you, really.
- Oh, man, you pay me back

24:02.170 --> 24:03.752
with a notebook full
of platinum records.

24:03.776 --> 24:05.378
That's how you pay me back.
All right?

24:05.403 --> 24:06.667
(both laugh)

24:07.651 --> 24:10.636
Boy, you... you really got a gift.

24:10.775 --> 24:12.824
- You know that, cuz?
- I don't, I don't know about that.

24:12.848 --> 24:14.940
Hey, hey, hey, hey, no
more of that, all right?

24:15.517 --> 24:16.714
No more looking away.

24:17.808 --> 24:20.136
Man, you see something you
want, you don't look away...

24:20.413 --> 24:21.413
you go get it.

24:22.818 --> 24:23.951
You hear me, cuz?

24:23.976 --> 24:25.077
(whispers): Yeah.

24:25.102 --> 24:26.659
- Uh?
- Yeah.

24:27.039 --> 24:28.284
(whispers): All right.

24:28.974 --> 24:30.511
All right, come here, you.

24:31.995 --> 24:33.339
Let's do it. (clears throat)

24:33.822 --> 24:35.175
(grunts, breathes deeply)

24:36.261 --> 24:37.573
I love you, cuz.

24:38.318 --> 24:39.448
I love you, too.

24:39.480 --> 24:40.784
(door opens, bells jingle)

24:41.409 --> 24:43.214
(blues music playing over speakers)

24:46.060 --> 24:47.479
Hey, Ricky.

24:50.589 --> 24:52.690
- It's me, William.
- I know who you are.

24:53.573 --> 24:55.183
Get the hell out my club.

25:08.363 --> 25:09.729
I'm dying, Ricky.

25:11.526 --> 25:14.168
(scoffs) You was dead to
me a long time ago, Willy.

25:15.003 --> 25:16.670
I had to go take care of her.

25:16.704 --> 25:18.534
Oh, come on, you think
I don't know that, cuz?

25:18.559 --> 25:19.667
I know that.

25:19.692 --> 25:21.276
I'm sorry. Cuz? Like cousin?

25:21.386 --> 25:22.597
This is your cousin?

25:22.683 --> 25:23.784
Yes.

25:24.446 --> 25:25.737
My son, Randall.

25:29.136 --> 25:30.417
Yeah, he look like you.

25:31.042 --> 25:34.001
I do? 'Cause, you know, I've
had a few people say that to me,

25:34.026 --> 25:36.790
but I don't really see the
re... I'll let you get to it.

25:39.081 --> 25:40.394
I wanted to come back.

25:40.683 --> 25:42.651
Oh, yeah? 'Cause I waited.

25:43.776 --> 25:45.565
For years, I waited to hear from you.

25:46.456 --> 25:48.073
We was gonna do something, man.

25:48.214 --> 25:49.413
RANDALL: I'm sorry, I know you guys

25:49.437 --> 25:51.071
are catching up with each other...

25:51.106 --> 25:53.273
but that makes you my
what, like, second cousin?

25:53.308 --> 25:55.104
Or is it cousin once remo... Okay.

25:57.901 --> 25:59.456
The hell happened to you, cuz?

26:00.515 --> 26:01.909
♪

26:09.924 --> 26:11.151
Hi, Mama.

26:11.292 --> 26:12.386
(gasps softly)

26:13.261 --> 26:15.136
I told you not to come.

26:15.386 --> 26:16.706
Of course I came.

26:40.104 --> 26:41.245
(breathes deeply)

26:42.466 --> 26:43.636
(sighs)

26:47.612 --> 26:49.323
I'm sicker than I let on, baby.

26:50.315 --> 26:51.776
It's okay.

26:52.331 --> 26:53.769
You'll... be okay.

26:57.711 --> 26:59.611
It won't be long, at least.

26:59.636 --> 27:01.077
I don't want you getting stuck here.

27:01.109 --> 27:02.643
Your life is in Memphis.

27:02.677 --> 27:04.168
- I won't keep you from it.
- Mama, I...

27:04.192 --> 27:06.446
Now, I want to hear
about all these clubs

27:06.481 --> 27:07.831
you're selling out.

27:08.269 --> 27:09.542
But you caught me in a nap,

27:09.567 --> 27:12.729
so why don't you go out and
explore the city a little.

27:13.425 --> 27:15.622
There's a bus stop right out front,

27:15.657 --> 27:17.386
and I know how you like the bus.

27:19.487 --> 27:20.661
And bring back some chicken.

27:20.695 --> 27:23.026
I'll cook you up something
special for dinner, okay?

27:23.433 --> 27:24.776
- Okay.
- Okay?

27:24.801 --> 27:25.715
- Yeah.
- All right.

27:25.740 --> 27:26.837
Gonna be okay, Mama?

27:26.862 --> 27:28.245
Yeah... Go on here, get out of here.

27:28.269 --> 27:29.464
- Okay.
- All right.

27:29.489 --> 27:30.917
♪

27:35.139 --> 27:38.003
♪ Catch a boat to England, baby ♪

27:38.873 --> 27:40.761
♪ Maybe to Spain ♪

27:42.670 --> 27:45.284
♪ Wherever I have gone ♪

27:46.221 --> 27:49.112
♪ Wherever I've been and gone ♪

27:49.618 --> 27:52.308
♪ Wherever I have gone ♪

27:52.333 --> 27:53.542
♪ The blues ♪

27:54.995 --> 27:56.667
♪ Are all the same ♪

28:03.838 --> 28:06.979
♪ Send out for whiskey, baby ♪

28:07.365 --> 28:08.999
♪ Send out for gin... ♪

28:09.119 --> 28:10.453
- Hi.
- Hello.

28:10.658 --> 28:12.159
Is this seat taken?

28:12.207 --> 28:14.042
♪ Me and room service, honey ♪

28:14.246 --> 28:17.064
♪ Me and room service, babe... ♪

28:17.089 --> 28:18.948
- William.
- (chuckles) Laurel.

28:19.222 --> 28:21.159
- (laughs)
- (laughs)

28:23.237 --> 28:25.167
♪ A life of sin ♪

28:32.065 --> 28:35.011
♪ Try another city, baby ♪

28:35.550 --> 28:37.659
♪ Another town ♪

28:39.407 --> 28:41.956
♪ Wherever I have gone ♪

28:42.823 --> 28:45.745
♪ Wherever I've been and gone ♪

28:46.314 --> 28:49.097
♪ Wherever I have gone ♪

28:49.122 --> 28:50.292
♪ The blues ♪

28:51.853 --> 28:54.154
♪ Are all the same. ♪

28:59.627 --> 29:01.667
- Oh, no, William, I can't, I can't.
- Come on, Mom.

29:01.692 --> 29:03.581
With the spoonfuls, I can't.
Please.

29:06.396 --> 29:09.940
I used to love waking
you up in the morning

29:09.965 --> 29:11.722
when you were a child.

29:12.455 --> 29:14.229
You looking up at me

29:15.425 --> 29:18.370
with those big, beautiful eyes.

29:19.013 --> 29:20.089
And now...

29:22.049 --> 29:25.940
..I'm down here... and you're up there.

29:32.057 --> 29:33.206
Do the poem.

29:34.134 --> 29:35.835
- The one I like, you know?
- Okay.

29:37.464 --> 29:38.839
Splendid against the night...

29:38.864 --> 29:40.128
Mm. Mm.

29:40.580 --> 29:41.925
The searchlights,

29:42.448 --> 29:44.526
- the tracers' arcs...
- Uh-huh.

29:44.551 --> 29:46.440
And the red flare of the bombs.

29:47.683 --> 29:48.850
(Dorothy groans softly)

29:48.875 --> 29:50.843
Filling the eye and the brain.

29:51.176 --> 29:52.229
Oh, good.

29:54.456 --> 29:57.472
- There's your poem, Mama.
- I love my poem.

29:57.497 --> 29:58.497
(sniffles)

29:59.767 --> 30:02.151
♪ Pharaoh ♪

30:07.197 --> 30:13.112
♪ Pharaoh ♪

30:14.081 --> 30:18.339
♪ Pharaoh army sure got drown dead ♪

30:18.560 --> 30:20.706
♪ Pharaoh. ♪

30:22.358 --> 30:24.693
WILLIAM: <i>I was ashamed
of what I had become.</i>

30:26.287 --> 30:28.675
All right, I'm well
aware I ruined everything.

30:30.566 --> 30:35.339
But now I'm dying, and I
just needed to say I'm sorry.

30:38.102 --> 30:39.651
You were good to me, cuz.

30:40.204 --> 30:41.511
I owed you that.

30:43.366 --> 30:44.401
Oh.

30:45.744 --> 30:47.222
And I owed you this.

30:49.289 --> 30:50.511
Now let's go.

30:53.996 --> 30:55.144
Hey, William.

30:56.685 --> 30:58.331
You, uh... (chuckles)

30:58.858 --> 31:00.003
You too sick to play?

31:02.857 --> 31:04.644
I'm never too sick to play.

31:05.628 --> 31:07.629
(band playing upbeat soul music)

31:12.253 --> 31:13.104
RANDALL: <i>Wait.</i>

31:13.129 --> 31:14.933
I know you, I know you.

31:15.067 --> 31:16.526
So that makes you...

31:17.514 --> 31:20.253
William's second cousin,
and your third cousin.

31:20.278 --> 31:22.913
Oh, so you get a cousin!

31:22.938 --> 31:24.572
You get a cousin!

31:24.597 --> 31:27.839
Everybody gets a cousin!

31:28.030 --> 31:29.864
Sorry, I was raised by white people.

31:29.889 --> 31:31.168
- (laughter)
- I don't know no better.

31:31.192 --> 31:32.124
(ringtone playing)

31:32.149 --> 31:34.847
Mm. That's my wife. Excuse me.

31:35.373 --> 31:36.800
Baby, you won't believe it.

31:36.825 --> 31:39.729
I'm up to 12 cousins of various forms.

31:39.754 --> 31:40.909
(laughs): Oh.

31:41.246 --> 31:43.047
The pictures are incredible.

31:43.189 --> 31:45.745
Is he actually playing on stage?

31:45.770 --> 31:47.331
He is. Here.

31:47.687 --> 31:49.011
(soul music continues)

31:50.665 --> 31:51.722
Wow.

31:52.627 --> 31:54.034
I wish you were here.

31:55.019 --> 31:56.761
- No, you don't.
<i>- RANDALL: No, I do.</i>

31:56.786 --> 31:58.854
Everything's better
with a little Beth on it.

31:59.121 --> 32:01.237
<i>You're the chocolate sauce
on my ice cream, girl.</i>

32:01.262 --> 32:02.276
Aw.

32:02.401 --> 32:03.535
Are you drunk?

32:03.560 --> 32:06.386
♪ Yeah, I may be a little drunk ♪

32:06.411 --> 32:09.880
♪ But that doesn't
mean it's not true. ♪

32:10.351 --> 32:11.862
You sound good.

32:11.887 --> 32:13.081
I feel good.

32:13.842 --> 32:16.675
Beth, I got a whole other family
down here. You got to see it.

32:16.700 --> 32:18.042
<i>Well, take lots of video.</i>

32:18.067 --> 32:19.104
I will.

32:19.479 --> 32:20.652
I love you, Beth.

32:20.899 --> 32:22.058
I love you.

32:22.409 --> 32:24.310
<i>Cousins!</i>

32:25.671 --> 32:27.237
♪

32:30.238 --> 32:32.672
♪ Diddly-bop-wop-boo! ♪

32:32.707 --> 32:33.800
(laughing)

32:38.161 --> 32:39.128
(baby cooing)

32:39.160 --> 32:41.472
DOROTHY: ♪ You are my sunshine ♪

32:41.782 --> 32:44.589
♪ My only sunshine ♪

32:44.614 --> 32:47.316
♪ You make me happy ♪ (chuckles)

32:47.341 --> 32:50.276
♪ When skies are gray. ♪

32:50.301 --> 32:52.635
♪ You'll never know, dear ♪

32:52.660 --> 32:55.394
♪ How much I love you ♪

32:56.128 --> 32:57.921
♪ So please don't take ♪

32:57.946 --> 33:00.381
♪ My sunshine away. ♪

33:01.702 --> 33:03.331
RANDALL: All right, old man.

33:04.245 --> 33:06.144
I let you sleep 'cause
we had a late night,

33:06.169 --> 33:08.644
but those ducks ain't
gonna wait all day.

33:10.745 --> 33:13.347
Well, actually they
probably will, but I won't.

33:13.525 --> 33:15.392
So here's what I was thinking.

33:15.637 --> 33:16.644
We can...

33:18.193 --> 33:19.393
(raspy breathing)

33:19.529 --> 33:20.542
Hey, William.

33:22.223 --> 33:23.698
(raspy breathing continues)

33:25.050 --> 33:26.261
Hey. It's okay.

33:28.805 --> 33:30.839
It's okay. I'm gonna get
you to the hospital, okay?

33:31.296 --> 33:32.479
It's okay.

33:33.001 --> 33:34.112
♪

34:06.060 --> 34:08.562
I don't understand. Last
night, he was smiling.

34:09.091 --> 34:10.793
- He was playing the piano.
- I know.

34:10.819 --> 34:11.871
- He was fine.
- I'm sorry.

34:11.897 --> 34:13.110
There's really no
timeline that makes sense

34:13.134 --> 34:14.754
of any of this at this stage.

34:14.779 --> 34:17.047
Honestly, it's a bit of a miracle
he was able to make the trip.

34:17.071 --> 34:18.271
But we haven't made the trip.

34:18.306 --> 34:20.139
We haven't even seen the ducks, man.

34:24.091 --> 34:25.121
Okay.

34:26.341 --> 34:28.943
Okay. Uh... (sniffles) I can do this.

34:29.255 --> 34:30.739
I said I would, and I will.

34:30.927 --> 34:33.263
(whispers): I said I
would, and I will, so...

34:34.333 --> 34:36.716
Uh, I need to get him home,
where he'll be comfortable.

34:36.974 --> 34:38.677
So be direct with me... can he fly?

34:38.818 --> 34:41.027
Because I have the means to
get a transport service...

34:41.052 --> 34:42.596
Mr. Pearson, I'm very sorry,

34:42.630 --> 34:45.771
but he's looking at hours
here, a day or so at best.

34:45.927 --> 34:48.208
No, no. He's-he's got
months, maybe more even.

34:48.380 --> 34:49.793
There's an experimental drug that

34:49.819 --> 34:51.842
- we're waiting for FDA approval...
- His organs are shutting down rapidly.

34:51.866 --> 34:52.706
His heart is extremely

34:52.732 --> 34:54.092
- compromised right now.
- Have you spoken to his

34:54.116 --> 34:55.630
- doctor in New York? Because...
- I have.

34:55.654 --> 34:57.574
- I'm sure you're very good at...
- Mr. Pearson.

34:57.747 --> 35:01.029
I'm very sorry, but you asked
me to be direct, so I will be.

35:01.802 --> 35:03.505
Your father is not
leaving this hospital.

35:05.661 --> 35:08.450
Now, I need to confirm, are
you his medical decision maker?

35:10.458 --> 35:12.169
(voice fading): And in
terms of heroic care,

35:12.193 --> 35:13.927
standard procedure is comfort and care,

35:13.961 --> 35:16.083
pain medication at maximum levels.

35:16.297 --> 35:18.099
No intubation, no resuscitation.

35:18.299 --> 35:19.388
♪

35:31.896 --> 35:33.380
(heart monitor beeping steadily)

35:35.063 --> 35:36.363
(sighs)

35:42.630 --> 35:43.732
(coughs)

35:44.705 --> 35:45.705
(inhales)

35:46.161 --> 35:47.310
(groans softly)

35:47.902 --> 35:49.419
No, no, no, no. You sleep.

35:53.708 --> 35:55.161
I spoke with the doctor.

35:58.708 --> 36:00.591
You knew you weren't coming home.

36:06.810 --> 36:08.568
What are you doing? Leave the...

36:13.200 --> 36:14.833
I got something for you.

36:17.333 --> 36:19.107
In the front of my bag, go ahead.

36:28.802 --> 36:30.677
Waiting for the right moment.

36:33.958 --> 36:35.141
(chuckles softly)

36:37.583 --> 36:39.363
(sniffles) I'm gonna call Beth.

36:39.388 --> 36:40.924
(clears throat) I'll have the girls here

36:40.948 --> 36:42.052
hugging you within hours.

36:42.077 --> 36:43.521
No, no, no, no, no, no, no.

36:45.195 --> 36:47.730
I said good-bye when
they were laying down.

36:51.107 --> 36:54.075
I want them to remember
looking up at me, not down.

36:55.777 --> 36:56.888
Up.

37:03.443 --> 37:05.505
Man, that was a hell of a thing you did,

37:05.540 --> 37:06.873
knocking on my door that day.

37:06.908 --> 37:09.576
(laughs) Come on, man.

37:12.990 --> 37:15.427
Roll all your windows down, Randall.

37:17.812 --> 37:19.357
Crank up the music.

37:21.355 --> 37:22.974
Grow out that 'fro.

37:25.732 --> 37:27.727
Let someone else make your bed.

37:28.685 --> 37:31.097
I like making my damn bed, old man.

37:33.286 --> 37:34.708
Then you make it.

37:37.810 --> 37:39.122
You deserve it.

37:42.130 --> 37:44.872
You deserve the beautiful
life you've made.

37:47.982 --> 37:49.919
You deserve everything, Randall.

37:53.355 --> 37:55.450
My beautiful boy.

38:01.517 --> 38:02.732
My son.

38:10.763 --> 38:12.685
I haven't had a happy life.

38:18.354 --> 38:22.552
Bad breaks and... bad choices.

38:25.686 --> 38:28.365
A life of almosts and could-haves.

38:31.788 --> 38:34.056
Some would call it sad, but I don't.

38:37.967 --> 38:40.497
'Cause the two best things in my life...

38:42.958 --> 38:46.419
... were the person in
the very beginning...

38:48.418 --> 38:50.521
... and the person at the very end.

38:54.687 --> 38:57.615
That's a pretty good thing
to be able to say, I think.

38:59.199 --> 39:00.763
I think so, too.

39:03.199 --> 39:04.372
(labored breathing)

39:12.419 --> 39:13.849
I'm a little scared.

39:15.638 --> 39:17.052
(labored breathing continues)

39:18.677 --> 39:20.010
(sniffles)

39:27.216 --> 39:28.255
(coughs)

39:28.280 --> 39:30.044
You're okay, Dad.

39:30.410 --> 39:31.505
Mm-hmm.

39:36.122 --> 39:37.380
You're good.

39:38.544 --> 39:39.591
Just breathe.

39:39.616 --> 39:40.616
Mm-hmm.

39:40.916 --> 39:42.974
Come on, now, breathe with me.

39:45.896 --> 39:47.216
(breathing deeply)

39:47.572 --> 39:49.068
There you go.

39:52.949 --> 39:54.482
There you go.

39:57.784 --> 39:59.052
♪

